WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:08.050 --> 00:00:09.760
- [laughing evilly]

2
00:00:12.930 --> 00:00:16.220
[eerie whisper]
- [gasps]

3
00:00:16.266 --> 00:00:19.136
[tense music]

4
00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:23.476
♪ ♪

5
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:28.280
[breathing heavily]

6
00:00:31.240 --> 00:00:34.280
[footsteps approaching]

7
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

8
00:00:49.258 --> 00:00:51.128
[screeching]

9
00:00:51.176 --> 00:00:52.926
- Henry. what are you doing?

10
00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:57.140
- Mom. I saw him.
- Hey. it’s okay.

11
00:00:57.182 --> 00:00:59.482
- I saw him move.
and I heard his voice.

12
00:00:59.518 --> 00:01:03.098
He whispered to me in the dark.

13
00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:05.146
- What did he say?

14
00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:09.650
- He said we’re
all going to die.

15
00:01:09.695 --> 00:01:12.325
♪ ♪

16
00:01:12.364 --> 00:01:14.664
- Henry. sweetheart.
come out of there.

17
00:01:17.202 --> 00:01:19.542
Let’s get back to bed.

18
00:01:22.666 --> 00:01:25.666
Now. listen to me.

19
00:01:25.711 --> 00:01:27.671
No one is going to die.

20
00:01:27.713 --> 00:01:30.173
And we talked about this.
didn’t we. Henry?

21
00:01:30.215 --> 00:01:32.005
There’s no such thing as ghosts.

22
00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:34.300
- But when Nana died.
you said she left her body

23
00:01:34.344 --> 00:01:35.854
and went to heaven.

24
00:01:35.887 --> 00:01:37.677
That’s a ghost.

25
00:01:37.723 --> 00:01:39.063
- That’s different.

26
00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:42.689
- What about Jesus?
He’s a ghost. the Holy Ghost.

27
00:01:42.728 --> 00:01:44.188
It says so in the Bible.

28
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:46.979
- Henry. I know moving
into a new house

29
00:01:47.024 --> 00:01:49.114
can be a little scary.

30
00:01:49.151 --> 00:01:52.201
especially a house
as big and old as this.

31
00:01:52.237 --> 00:01:53.777
but you’ll get used to it.

32
00:01:53.822 --> 00:01:56.492
I promise.

33
00:01:56.533 --> 00:01:58.663
- Well. at least
there’s one good thing.

34
00:01:58.702 --> 00:02:01.002
- And what’s that?

35
00:02:01.038 --> 00:02:03.708
- At least Joseph is here.

36
00:02:03.749 --> 00:02:05.079
- What?

37
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:10.205
♪ ♪

38
00:02:10.255 --> 00:02:12.545
- To protect me from the ghost.

39
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:14.681
- [sighs. chuckles softly]
Right.

40
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:21.022
Well...
[clears throat]

41
00:02:21.058 --> 00:02:23.848
there...

42
00:02:23.894 --> 00:02:26.024
you go.

43
00:02:26.063 --> 00:02:28.573
- Joseph says
that sometimes a ghost

44
00:02:28.607 --> 00:02:31.187
might be hiding in the last
place you’d ever suspect.

45
00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:33.744
- Well. Joseph is wrong.

46
00:02:33.779 --> 00:02:36.779
There’s no such thing as ghosts.

47
00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:39.623
just like there’s no such thing
as talking dolls.

48
00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:41.870
They’re all just a part
of our imagination. right?

49
00:02:41.912 --> 00:02:45.922
- Miss Cunningham says I have
a very active imagination.

50
00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.497
- A little too active.

51
00:02:48.543 --> 00:02:51.053
- Can we come in and sleep
with you and Dad again tonight?

52
00:02:51.088 --> 00:02:52.918
- Henry.
- Just for tonight?

53
00:02:52.964 --> 00:02:54.764
- Henry. we talked about this.

54
00:02:54.800 --> 00:02:56.890
You’re a big boy now.

55
00:02:56.927 --> 00:02:58.927
You got this. okay?

56
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:00.220
- Okay.

57
00:03:00.263 --> 00:03:02.063
- Okay.

58
00:03:02.099 --> 00:03:05.139
Good night. sweetheart.

59
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:07.435
- Don’t forget Joseph.

60
00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:10.939
- Good night. Joseph.

61
00:03:10.982 --> 00:03:12.652
- Leave it on.

62
00:03:19.116 --> 00:03:21.076
[door creaking]

63
00:03:21.118 --> 00:03:28.208
♪ ♪

64
00:03:33.338 --> 00:03:35.218
We’ve got this. Joseph.

65
00:03:35.257 --> 00:03:39.337
♪ ♪

66
00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:42.176
- We sure do.

67
00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:49.312
♪ ♪

68
00:04:15.714 --> 00:04:17.554
[Henry screams]

69
00:04:17.591 --> 00:04:20.721
[playful spooky music]

70
00:04:20.761 --> 00:04:27.681
♪ ♪

71
00:04:35.066 --> 00:04:38.026
[dramatic music]

72
00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:44.029
♪ ♪

73
00:04:44.075 --> 00:04:46.535
- Where’s the backup?

74
00:04:46.578 --> 00:04:48.368
- Should have kicked
in immediately.

75
00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:50.253
- Anything like this
ever happened before?

76
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.540
- Once in ’15. Obama
was in the Oval.

77
00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:54.145
1:00 in the afternoon. didn’t
even realize what happened

78
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:55.419
till we came and got him.

79
00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:56.856
- So it’s not that
big a deal. then?

80
00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.050
- It’s a power outage

81
00:04:58.089 --> 00:05:00.469
in the most secure house
in the world. Simms.

82
00:05:00.509 --> 00:05:03.009
It’s a big deal. Get the kids.
- Roger that. right.

83
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:04.143
- Henry?

84
00:05:04.179 --> 00:05:05.179
Henry?

85
00:05:05.222 --> 00:05:06.722
- Coop. what’s going on?

86
00:05:06.765 --> 00:05:08.576
- Potomac Power says no
one else in D. C. is affected.

87
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.310
It’s just us. Mr. President.

88
00:05:10.352 --> 00:05:12.413
So we need to get you and your
family downstairs right now.

89
00:05:12.437 --> 00:05:13.857
- Downstairs downstairs?

90
00:05:13.897 --> 00:05:16.187
- Yeah. it’s just a precaution.
strictly protocol.

91
00:05:16.233 --> 00:05:17.376
We’ll take
the elevator down. sir.

92
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.400
It’s on a backup generator.

93
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:21.284
- This ever happened before?

94
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:23.911
- Mommy. Joseph’s gone.
They took him.

95
00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:25.619
- Who... who took him?
- The ghosts.

96
00:05:25.659 --> 00:05:27.699
- They’re plural now.
- Ma’am. I’ll get the doll.

97
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:29.334
Why don’t you guys go
with Agent Simms?

98
00:05:29.371 --> 00:05:30.711
And I’ll meet you
at the elevator.

99
00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:32.457
- Thank you.
- Be careful Teddy.

100
00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:34.329
- This way. ma’am.
- I’ll be right there.

101
00:05:34.376 --> 00:05:37.206
♪ ♪

102
00:05:37.254 --> 00:05:38.764
- [knocks on door]
Grant. it’s me.

103
00:05:38.797 --> 00:05:40.917
- Yeah.
- Come on. we have to go.

104
00:05:40.966 --> 00:05:43.586
- All right. come in.

105
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:45.435
- What the hell are you doing?

106
00:05:45.470 --> 00:05:47.600
- [coughing]
- Give me that.

107
00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:49.450
What’s it look like?
I’m sticking it to the man.

108
00:05:49.474 --> 00:05:51.234
- We’re going to talk
about this later.

109
00:05:51.268 --> 00:05:52.828
Now we have to go.
- Where are we going?

110
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.233
- Basement.
- The basement. why?

111
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:57.822
- Here. just have
a breath mint... you stink.

112
00:05:57.858 --> 00:06:04.778
♪ ♪

113
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:22.553
[light clatter]

114
00:06:22.591 --> 00:06:29.681
♪ ♪

115
00:06:49.868 --> 00:06:51.658
- Call Spence. then Melanie.

116
00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:53.503
Tell them. uh. I’ll call them
on a hard line

117
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:54.828
once I get downstairs.

118
00:06:54.873 --> 00:06:57.673
Tell Melanie
to prep a statement.

119
00:06:57.709 --> 00:06:59.839
I don’t know.
Tell her to make something up.

120
00:06:59.878 --> 00:07:01.668
Tell her I’ll fill in the blanks

121
00:07:01.713 --> 00:07:03.803
once I know
what the hell is going on.

122
00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:05.050
All right.

123
00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:07.301
- What do you say. Henry?
- Thank you. Teddy.

124
00:07:07.344 --> 00:07:09.434
- Oh. you’re very welcome. sir.

125
00:07:09.471 --> 00:07:12.431
[dog panting]

126
00:07:12.474 --> 00:07:15.024
♪ ♪

127
00:07:15.060 --> 00:07:16.940
- We’re heading down.

128
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:19.808
♪ ♪

129
00:07:19.856 --> 00:07:22.776
[elevator whirs]

130
00:07:41.044 --> 00:07:44.174
- Great. No Wi-Fi.

131
00:07:44.214 --> 00:07:45.634
What?

132
00:07:47.592 --> 00:07:50.722
[sighs]
So how far down is it?

133
00:07:50.762 --> 00:07:53.562
- Five stories underground.

134
00:07:53.598 --> 00:07:55.728
- We. like. under attack
or something?

135
00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:59.727
- Of course not.
This is just a precaution.

136
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:02.691
Strictly routine.
- How do you know that?

137
00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:05.072
- Coop told me.
- I’m sure it’s nothing. ma’am.

138
00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:07.900
- It’s the ghost.
This house is haunted.

139
00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:11.736
- Henry.
[dog growls. barking]

140
00:08:14.619 --> 00:08:17.499
- Sorry. he’s a little anxious.

141
00:08:17.539 --> 00:08:21.749
- [growling. barks]

142
00:08:21.793 --> 00:08:23.793
- Mommy!
- I’m right here. honey.

143
00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:26.507
- Everybody stay calm.

144
00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:28.168
- Ow!

145
00:08:32.303 --> 00:08:35.603
[lights click. elevator whirs]

146
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:38.890
♪ ♪

147
00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:40.095
Bad boy.

148
00:08:40.145 --> 00:08:41.815
- [growls]

149
00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:46.109
- Roger that.

150
00:08:47.777 --> 00:08:50.777
- Going back upstairs?
- Yes. sir. Power’s back on.

151
00:08:50.822 --> 00:08:52.550
Everything’s fine.
You can all go back to bed.

152
00:08:52.574 --> 00:08:59.621
♪ ♪

153
00:08:59.622 --> 00:09:07.622
- ♪ No... no... nobody
can stop me ♪

154
00:09:09.007 --> 00:09:10.627
- Hey. it’s Jake.

155
00:09:10.675 --> 00:09:13.175
I want to thank you guys
for your support.

156
00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:14.799
your messages. your prayers.

157
00:09:14.846 --> 00:09:18.216
They really mean a lot
to me. Devon. and Lexy.

158
00:09:18.266 --> 00:09:19.636
We’re doing better.

159
00:09:19.684 --> 00:09:22.484
We’re all finding
our own ways to cope.

160
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:24.150
Mine’s been to focus on my art.

161
00:09:24.189 --> 00:09:25.979
♪ ♪

162
00:09:26.024 --> 00:09:27.484
- I’ve always been
the kind of boy

163
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:30.315
who likes to play with dolls.
but I’m not a kid anymore.

164
00:09:30.361 --> 00:09:31.821
Time to put away
childish things.

165
00:09:31.863 --> 00:09:36.123
This is going to be
my final piece in this genre.

166
00:09:36.159 --> 00:09:38.659
my last word on the subject...

167
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:42.043
An exposé on the darkness
behind the innocent facades

168
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:44.332
of the most popular
mass-marketed dolls

169
00:09:44.375 --> 00:09:45.995
of the last 100 years.

170
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.594
The horror that is Kewpie.

171
00:09:48.630 --> 00:09:52.010
Barbie. Raggedy Ann and Andy.
Chatty Cathy. Baby Nancy.

172
00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.840
Cabbage Patch. American Girl.

173
00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.555
But as you can see.

174
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:58.555
the last doll I really
need to finish this

175
00:09:58.598 --> 00:10:01.268
and. well. to finally move on
with my life.

176
00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:04.149
you guessed it... Good Guy.

177
00:10:04.187 --> 00:10:07.857
Problem is there doesn’t
seem to be any left.

178
00:10:07.899 --> 00:10:10.479
I haven’t been able
to find one anywhere.

179
00:10:10.527 --> 00:10:13.487
No one has for over a year.

180
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:17.030
But I heard a rumor there still
might be one more out there.

181
00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:18.665
And I’d be willing to pay.

182
00:10:18.701 --> 00:10:21.411
So. if anyone sees
this Good Guy doll

183
00:10:21.454 --> 00:10:25.714
or even hears about it.
please get in touch.

184
00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:30.090
I really need to get
my hands on that doll.

185
00:10:31.923 --> 00:10:34.553
[epic music]

186
00:10:34.592 --> 00:10:38.512
- Good morning. everyone.
All: Good morning.

187
00:10:38.555 --> 00:10:40.105
- Okay.

188
00:10:40.140 --> 00:10:43.390
The White House experienced
a brief power outage last night

189
00:10:43.434 --> 00:10:46.234
from 11:48 p. m.
Until 12:05 a. m.

190
00:10:46.271 --> 00:10:49.231
The problem was apparently
a mechanical malfunction.

191
00:10:49.274 --> 00:10:51.034
but the power
has been fully restored.

192
00:10:51.067 --> 00:10:53.437
and the president’s schedule
has not been affected.

193
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.816
Now. moving on to
the crime bill.

194
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:57.258
[reporters shouting]
- Speaker. question.

195
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:58.782
- Gretchen?

196
00:10:58.825 --> 00:11:00.745
- Has Homeland Security
ruled out the possibility

197
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:03.155
of criminal or
terrorist-related activity

198
00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:04.714
or espionage?

199
00:11:04.747 --> 00:11:06.747
- We’re still looking
into the exact nature

200
00:11:06.791 --> 00:11:08.001
of the malfunction.

201
00:11:08.042 --> 00:11:09.922
- So you don’t really
know what went wrong?

202
00:11:09.961 --> 00:11:12.091
- Not yet. but the president
and his family

203
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:13.590
were never
in any serious danger.

204
00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:15.171
- But isn’t it true
the situation

205
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:17.361
was considered serious enough
to move the First Family down

206
00:11:17.385 --> 00:11:19.595
to the bunker?
- Uh...

207
00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:22.467
- The president’s son
did a TikTok on it.

208
00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:25.425
[laughter]
- Yeah. of course.

209
00:11:25.476 --> 00:11:27.806
Um. I’d characterize
the incident

210
00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:30.944
as a serious inconvenience
and annoyance to the family.

211
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:33.282
but. yes.
as a matter of protocol.

212
00:11:33.318 --> 00:11:34.818
steps were taken to escort them

213
00:11:34.861 --> 00:11:37.071
to the Presidential
Emergency Operations Center.

214
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:39.953
But the power was restored
before that became necessary.

215
00:11:39.991 --> 00:11:42.951
- Would you say that
this incident could point

216
00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:46.464
to larger concerns about
security in the White House

217
00:11:46.497 --> 00:11:50.747
and. by extension.
the nation as a whole?

218
00:11:50.793 --> 00:11:53.133
- James Collins
was elected on a platform

219
00:11:53.171 --> 00:11:55.261
of unprecedented transparency.

220
00:11:55.298 --> 00:11:58.928
The American people have seen
every tax form. phone record.

221
00:11:58.968 --> 00:12:00.298
every report card dating back

222
00:12:00.345 --> 00:12:02.975
to the president’s
halcyon days in kindergarten

223
00:12:03.014 --> 00:12:05.064
at PS 22 in Jersey City.

224
00:12:05.099 --> 00:12:07.389
As this nation’s
first duly elected

225
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:09.265
independent commander in chief.

226
00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:12.362
he’s beholden to no political
party or corporate agenda.

227
00:12:12.398 --> 00:12:15.228
President Collins has vowed
to heal this nation

228
00:12:15.276 --> 00:12:16.486
and bring us together

229
00:12:16.527 --> 00:12:18.447
after years of division
and partisanship.

230
00:12:18.488 --> 00:12:20.988
So if there are ever
any concerns about security

231
00:12:21.032 --> 00:12:23.492
or anything else. I assure you.

232
00:12:23.534 --> 00:12:25.494
you and everyone else
in this room

233
00:12:25.536 --> 00:12:27.826
will be the first
to know about it.

234
00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:31.002
Okay. let’s get back
to that crime bill.

235
00:12:31.042 --> 00:12:34.002
[dramatic music]

236
00:12:34.045 --> 00:12:41.185
♪ ♪

237
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:50.899
- No more TikTok.

238
00:12:53.564 --> 00:12:55.614
- You can’t censor me. Mom.

239
00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:58.190
not when you’re married
to President Transparency.

240
00:12:58.236 --> 00:13:00.396
- Stop calling your father that.

241
00:13:00.446 --> 00:13:03.406
This isn’t the same
as exposing my hideous taste

242
00:13:03.449 --> 00:13:05.409
in drapes in the East Room.
- Hmm.

243
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:07.388
Well. "Architectural Digest"
must have agreed with me.

244
00:13:07.412 --> 00:13:08.622
because they reposted that.

245
00:13:08.663 --> 00:13:10.373
- Grant. we’re speaking
here about matters

246
00:13:10.415 --> 00:13:12.635
of national security.

247
00:13:12.667 --> 00:13:15.747
- Mom. the drapes
aren’t that bad. okay?

248
00:13:15.795 --> 00:13:17.955
I just think that if you’re
going to brand yourself

249
00:13:18.006 --> 00:13:21.586
as President Transparency
and you basically sell off

250
00:13:21.634 --> 00:13:23.894
the family’s privacy
to win an election.

251
00:13:23.928 --> 00:13:26.008
you got to take
the bad with the good.

252
00:13:26.055 --> 00:13:29.055
And I’m sure Dad would agree
with me on that. right. Dad?

253
00:13:29.100 --> 00:13:31.060
- You don’t leave me
with much of a choice.

254
00:13:31.102 --> 00:13:32.913
- Oh. and let me remind you.
um. I will be old enough

255
00:13:32.937 --> 00:13:36.567
to vote in the next election.
- Yeah. I’ll alert the media.

256
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:39.027
- Hey. listen to this.
- Hmm?

257
00:13:39.068 --> 00:13:41.238
- "William Henry Harrison
was the first president

258
00:13:41.279 --> 00:13:43.909
"to die in the White House.

259
00:13:43.948 --> 00:13:47.408
"His ghost is said
to haunt the attic.

260
00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:50.082
"And Dolley Madison
supposedly haunts

261
00:13:50.121 --> 00:13:52.081
"the Rose Garden in springtime.

262
00:13:52.123 --> 00:13:54.583
protecting the buds
from an early frost."

263
00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:57.545
- Henry. where did
you get that book?

264
00:13:57.587 --> 00:14:01.757
- From the gift shop
on the tour downstairs.

265
00:14:01.799 --> 00:14:04.589
"The most notorious ghosts
in the White House

266
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:06.885
"involve
President Abraham Lincoln

267
00:14:06.929 --> 00:14:08.599
"and his family.

268
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:11.769
"Mary Lincoln believed
the White House was haunted

269
00:14:11.809 --> 00:14:13.769
"by the ghost of her son Willie.

270
00:14:13.811 --> 00:14:18.111
who died tragically
of typhoid in 1862."

271
00:14:18.149 --> 00:14:23.069
♪ ♪

272
00:14:23.112 --> 00:14:24.912
What’s typhoid?

273
00:14:24.947 --> 00:14:26.617
- A disease people got
here in D. C.

274
00:14:26.657 --> 00:14:28.407
From all the contaminated water.

275
00:14:28.451 --> 00:14:31.451
- Grant.
- [slurps]

276
00:14:31.496 --> 00:14:34.246
- How old was he...

277
00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:36.380
the president’s son.

278
00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:38.957
when he died?

279
00:14:39.003 --> 00:14:40.423
- 11.

280
00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:42.803
Um. gosh. I’m late.

281
00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:45.970
I have a meeting
with the decorator.

282
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:48.050
Henry. give me that book.

283
00:14:48.096 --> 00:14:49.806
Thank you.

284
00:14:49.847 --> 00:14:53.137
- Daddy. Joseph doesn’t want to
come to school with me today.

285
00:14:53.184 --> 00:14:55.694
He wants to go to work with you.

286
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:58.438
He wants to see the Oval Office.

287
00:15:00.191 --> 00:15:01.941
- Have fun.

288
00:15:01.984 --> 00:15:06.994
♪ ♪

289
00:15:07.031 --> 00:15:11.161
- Okay.
- [coughs]

290
00:15:11.202 --> 00:15:18.332
♪ ♪

291
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:25.008
- We were hacked.

292
00:15:25.049 --> 00:15:27.179
- Russia?

293
00:15:27.218 --> 00:15:28.718
North Korea?

294
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:31.181
- We don’t know yet.
It could be domestic.

295
00:15:31.222 --> 00:15:33.852
It could be some resentful
loner with rage issues

296
00:15:33.891 --> 00:15:37.101
working out
of his parents’ basement.

297
00:15:37.145 --> 00:15:38.525
- Did they get anything?

298
00:15:38.563 --> 00:15:40.653
- So far. it looks
like the breach didn’t get

299
00:15:40.690 --> 00:15:43.030
beyond the power grid.

300
00:15:43.067 --> 00:15:44.527
- What did they want?

301
00:15:44.569 --> 00:15:46.569
- Possibly just to see
if they could do it.

302
00:15:46.612 --> 00:15:48.862
- Or possibly to get a peek
behind the curtain.

303
00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:51.736
see how everything works.
plan future attacks.

304
00:15:51.784 --> 00:15:55.044
- How does this happen here?
- We need to check our seals.

305
00:15:55.079 --> 00:15:57.709
We may have a leak.
- In the White House?

306
00:15:57.748 --> 00:15:59.378
- How are we going
to message this?

307
00:15:59.417 --> 00:16:00.877
- We can’t message this.

308
00:16:00.918 --> 00:16:03.298
No. we can’t let this get out.
We keep it between us.

309
00:16:03.337 --> 00:16:08.217
- Spence. that’s not
very vice presidential of you.

310
00:16:08.259 --> 00:16:11.889
We are not going to bury this.

311
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:15.519
We’re certainly not
going to message this.

312
00:16:15.558 --> 00:16:18.348
We’re going to tell
people the truth.

313
00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:19.734
We were hacked.

314
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:22.400
- The United States government
was hacked?

315
00:16:22.440 --> 00:16:25.860
- It’s not exactly
unprecedented.

316
00:16:25.902 --> 00:16:28.822
Our numbers will survive.
- [chuckles wryly]

317
00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:36.873
So. Mr. President.
who is your new bodyguard?

318
00:16:36.913 --> 00:16:39.253
- That’s Henry’s.

319
00:16:39.290 --> 00:16:41.170
Yeah.

320
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:43.749
He asked me to bring it
to work today.

321
00:16:43.794 --> 00:16:45.594
Guess what his name is.

322
00:16:49.967 --> 00:16:52.797
What’s your name?

323
00:16:52.845 --> 00:16:56.555
- Hi. I’m Joseph. and
I’m your friend till the end.

324
00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:59.439
Hidey-Ho!
Ha ha ha.

325
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:00.977
- Oh.
[scoffs]

326
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:03.440
- It’s just...
It’s a weird coincidence.

327
00:17:03.481 --> 00:17:07.361
Henry finding a doll
with that name.

328
00:17:07.401 --> 00:17:08.861
Anyway...

329
00:17:08.903 --> 00:17:10.823
[knock at door. door opens]

330
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:14.413
- Mr. President. your 11:00
is waiting in the East Room.

331
00:17:14.450 --> 00:17:15.830
- Thank you. Samantha.

332
00:17:15.868 --> 00:17:18.118
Can’t keep the governor
of Rhode Island waiting.

333
00:17:18.162 --> 00:17:19.962
Thank you.

334
00:17:19.997 --> 00:17:25.287
♪ ♪

335
00:17:25.336 --> 00:17:27.416
[door opens. closes]

336
00:17:27.463 --> 00:17:33.218
♪ ♪

337
00:17:33.219 --> 00:17:41.219
[exciting rock music]

338
00:17:42.061 --> 00:17:45.901
♪ ♪

339
00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:46.690
- Okay.

340
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:50.652
♪ ♪

341
00:17:50.695 --> 00:17:52.285
You asked for it.

342
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:54.661
♪ ♪

343
00:17:54.699 --> 00:17:56.079
So here it is.

344
00:17:56.117 --> 00:18:00.197
♪ ♪

345
00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.496
If I have to stoop

346
00:18:01.539 --> 00:18:04.209
to thirst-trap TikToks
twice a day...

347
00:18:04.250 --> 00:18:06.920
- ♪ ’Cause you know
that I can ♪

348
00:18:06.961 --> 00:18:08.801
- If this is
what it’s going to take

349
00:18:08.838 --> 00:18:10.298
for me to find my sister...

350
00:18:10.339 --> 00:18:13.509
♪ ♪

351
00:18:13.551 --> 00:18:15.431
Congratulations. everyone.

352
00:18:15.469 --> 00:18:19.519
♪ ♪

353
00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:21.347
You fucking win.

354
00:18:21.392 --> 00:18:23.352
♪ ♪

355
00:18:23.394 --> 00:18:25.524
Okay?
[breathing heavily]

356
00:18:25.563 --> 00:18:28.523
So. now that I got
your attention.

357
00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:30.476
last year on Christmas Eve...

358
00:18:30.526 --> 00:18:32.686
[holiday music]

359
00:18:32.737 --> 00:18:35.107
My mother
was murdered in cold blood.

360
00:18:35.156 --> 00:18:39.116
[Chucky laughing]

361
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.450
My sister Caroline
was kidnapped.

362
00:18:42.496 --> 00:18:45.246
[tires squealing]

363
00:18:46.876 --> 00:18:50.496
I miss them both
more than I can say.

364
00:18:50.546 --> 00:18:53.046
This is the most
recent picture of her.

365
00:18:53.090 --> 00:18:57.720
So. if anyone has any intel
on her whereabouts.

366
00:18:57.762 --> 00:19:00.142
please contact me.

367
00:19:00.181 --> 00:19:03.431
[sighs] And. Caroline.
if you’re watching.

368
00:19:03.476 --> 00:19:05.476
I love you.

369
00:19:05.519 --> 00:19:09.729
I’m going to find you. and I’m
going to bring you home.

370
00:19:09.774 --> 00:19:11.944
And the most important thing...

371
00:19:11.984 --> 00:19:16.244
Be very. very careful
with that doll.

372
00:19:16.280 --> 00:19:18.910
[school bell ringing.
indistinct chatter]

373
00:19:18.949 --> 00:19:21.239
- Hey. Henry. where’s your doll?

374
00:19:21.285 --> 00:19:25.535
- Bradley. this is Teddy.
He’s my Secret Service agent.

375
00:19:25.581 --> 00:19:27.961
He’s basically my bodyguard.

376
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:31.090
So. you know. don’t even think
of pulling any crap.

377
00:19:31.128 --> 00:19:32.838
- [chuckles]
You think that’s a good idea?

378
00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:34.170
Don’t you want to make friends?

379
00:19:34.215 --> 00:19:36.885
- I have you. You’re my friend.
- Yeah. I am.

380
00:19:36.926 --> 00:19:38.966
But. Henry. you need friends
that you can talk to

381
00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:41.971
and play with. go to when
you’re feeling sad and scared.

382
00:19:42.014 --> 00:19:44.184
- Like I do with you and Joseph.

383
00:19:44.225 --> 00:19:47.145
- Yeah. but someone
your own age...

384
00:19:47.186 --> 00:19:48.476
real.

385
00:19:48.521 --> 00:19:50.731
You remind me of my son Malcolm.

386
00:19:50.773 --> 00:19:52.733
- Does Malcolm have
a Good Guy doll?

387
00:19:52.775 --> 00:19:54.285
- Well. he’s more
of a sports guy.

388
00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:57.608
but he’s a good kid. smart kid.
big heart. just like you.

389
00:19:57.655 --> 00:19:59.955
- Joseph’s got a big heart. too.

390
00:19:59.990 --> 00:20:02.620
At night.
when I listen really close.

391
00:20:02.660 --> 00:20:04.620
I can hear it beating.

392
00:20:04.662 --> 00:20:08.582
[eerie music]

393
00:20:08.624 --> 00:20:15.594
♪ ♪

394
00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:17.591
[siren whoops]

395
00:20:17.633 --> 00:20:21.553
♪ ♪

396
00:20:21.595 --> 00:20:23.555
[door closes]

397
00:20:23.597 --> 00:20:30.557
♪ ♪

398
00:20:30.604 --> 00:20:32.484
[indistinct chatter]

399
00:20:32.523 --> 00:20:35.233
- Sam. who’s my next victim?

400
00:20:35.276 --> 00:20:36.776
- Your wife.

401
00:20:38.696 --> 00:20:41.196
You’re going over color swatches

402
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:42.780
up in the residence.

403
00:20:42.825 --> 00:20:44.955
Remember?
- Yes. okay.

404
00:20:44.994 --> 00:20:46.834
- You’re already late.

405
00:20:46.871 --> 00:20:49.831
- Yeah. I just. uh. need
a minute.

406
00:20:52.501 --> 00:20:55.461
[suspenseful music]

407
00:20:55.504 --> 00:21:02.394
♪ ♪

408
00:21:44.929 --> 00:21:47.179
- Henry come by the office?

409
00:21:47.223 --> 00:21:48.393
- Uh. no. sir.

410
00:21:48.432 --> 00:21:51.352
He’s en route home from school
as we speak.

411
00:21:55.064 --> 00:21:57.194
- Who was in there?

412
00:21:57.233 --> 00:22:00.743
- Um. Spence came back
for his briefcase.

413
00:22:00.778 --> 00:22:02.528
Melanie was with him.

414
00:22:02.571 --> 00:22:04.161
Coop did his sweep.

415
00:22:04.198 --> 00:22:07.488
And me.

416
00:22:07.535 --> 00:22:08.795
Why?

417
00:22:10.579 --> 00:22:12.409
- Who’s the comedian?

418
00:22:14.375 --> 00:22:16.215
- Excuse me?

419
00:22:21.382 --> 00:22:22.722
- Never mind.

420
00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:24.508
Coop. let’s go.

421
00:22:24.552 --> 00:22:26.472
- Yes. sir.

422
00:22:26.512 --> 00:22:29.352
[playful spooky music]

423
00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:36.400
♪ ♪

424
00:22:53.706 --> 00:22:56.666
- Can we get a smoothie?

425
00:22:56.709 --> 00:22:58.419
- Henry. what’s wrong?

426
00:23:00.421 --> 00:23:03.721
- I don’t want to go in.
I’m scared.

427
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.257
- Henry...

428
00:23:06.302 --> 00:23:09.392
you have to cut
this shit out. okay?

429
00:23:09.430 --> 00:23:12.770
You’re freaking out Mom and Dad.

430
00:23:12.808 --> 00:23:14.728
- Teddy believes me.

431
00:23:14.768 --> 00:23:17.768
Don’t you. Teddy?

432
00:23:17.813 --> 00:23:20.363
- You shouldn’t encourage him.

433
00:23:20.399 --> 00:23:27.319
♪ ♪

434
00:23:41.587 --> 00:23:45.417
[wind whistling eerily]

435
00:23:45.466 --> 00:23:52.466
♪ ♪

436
00:23:56.477 --> 00:23:58.847
- No. it’s not blue.
It’s seafoam.

437
00:23:58.896 --> 00:24:00.896
- Okay.

438
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:03.690
I like it.

439
00:24:03.734 --> 00:24:05.994
- N-no. they’re...
They’re too dark.

440
00:24:06.028 --> 00:24:08.318
- Charlotte...
- [sighs]

441
00:24:08.364 --> 00:24:10.324
- We’ve been here for months.

442
00:24:10.366 --> 00:24:12.116
If you don’t make a decision.

443
00:24:12.159 --> 00:24:13.989
you could miss your window
of opportunity.

444
00:24:14.036 --> 00:24:15.116
- Don’t be so pessimistic.

445
00:24:15.162 --> 00:24:17.212
"The Post" said just
the other day.

446
00:24:17.247 --> 00:24:18.867
you’re going to be a two-termer.

447
00:24:18.916 --> 00:24:20.826
- Oh.

448
00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:22.626
That’s what "The Post" said?

449
00:24:22.670 --> 00:24:25.380
Well. then no rush.
- You don’t understand.

450
00:24:25.422 --> 00:24:29.892
Jackie and Betty and Michelle
all set a very high bar.

451
00:24:29.927 --> 00:24:31.597
I mean. everybody
is watching me.

452
00:24:31.637 --> 00:24:34.467
Our son is watching me.
I just need to get it right.

453
00:24:34.515 --> 00:24:36.485
- Hey. come here.

454
00:24:36.517 --> 00:24:39.057
[soft music]

455
00:24:39.103 --> 00:24:41.153
I just don’t want you
to put too much pressure

456
00:24:41.188 --> 00:24:43.478
on yourself. okay?

457
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:45.444
Give yourself a break.

458
00:24:45.484 --> 00:24:49.824
- I need to keep busy. James.
just like you.

459
00:24:49.863 --> 00:24:52.413
♪ ♪

460
00:24:52.449 --> 00:24:53.909
- I know.

461
00:24:55.744 --> 00:24:58.714
- Dad. where’s Joseph?

462
00:24:58.747 --> 00:25:01.167
- He’s in your room.

463
00:25:01.208 --> 00:25:04.538
And I think he found the
Oval Office very interesting.

464
00:25:07.131 --> 00:25:10.301
- Teddy. will you
sweep my room first?

465
00:25:11.719 --> 00:25:13.679
- Happy to. sir.

466
00:25:13.721 --> 00:25:16.011
- Hey.

467
00:25:16.056 --> 00:25:18.056
[door closes]

468
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:21.020
[suspenseful music]

469
00:25:21.061 --> 00:25:28.151
♪ ♪

470
00:26:27.836 --> 00:26:30.796
[Chucky laughs evilly]

471
00:26:30.839 --> 00:26:36.299
♪ ♪

472
00:26:36.345 --> 00:26:38.475
[running footsteps. door opens]

473
00:26:38.514 --> 00:26:42.183
[Charlotte screams]
No!

474
00:26:42.184 --> 00:26:50.184
- A lot of you
have posted questions

475
00:26:51.068 --> 00:26:52.796
about what really happened
here in Hackensack

476
00:26:52.820 --> 00:26:54.297
and at the School
of the Incarnate Lord.

477
00:26:54.321 --> 00:26:55.861
[eerie screech]

478
00:26:55.906 --> 00:26:59.366
Like at the now-infamous town
rally a couple of years ago.

479
00:26:59.409 --> 00:27:02.869
how exactly did Junior Wheeler
sneak backstage.

480
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:04.043
decapitate our principal...

481
00:27:04.081 --> 00:27:05.541
- [screams]
- And sneak back

482
00:27:05.582 --> 00:27:07.542
into the audience
without anyone noticing?

483
00:27:07.584 --> 00:27:10.384
Some of you have
also noticed a figure

484
00:27:10.420 --> 00:27:12.960
from a lot of the footage
and pics from that time...

485
00:27:13.006 --> 00:27:15.046
A Good Guy doll.

486
00:27:15.092 --> 00:27:16.132
We all know the connection

487
00:27:16.176 --> 00:27:17.966
that Good Guy dolls have
with Hackensack.

488
00:27:18.011 --> 00:27:21.221
going all the way back to
the ’60s and Charles Lee Ray.

489
00:27:21.265 --> 00:27:23.065
one of the most vicious
serial killers

490
00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:24.520
of the late 20th century.

491
00:27:24.560 --> 00:27:26.980
who was gunned down
in a Chicago toy store in ’88

492
00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:29.860
and went on to become an even
more bizarre urban legend

493
00:27:29.898 --> 00:27:32.938
than I bet he himself
could have originally imagined.

494
00:27:32.985 --> 00:27:36.115
even in the darkest corners
of his twisted mind.

495
00:27:36.155 --> 00:27:38.415
Some of you have also asked
the unthinkable.

496
00:27:38.448 --> 00:27:40.658
Is there really a connection
between that doll

497
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:42.411
and all the murders?

498
00:27:42.452 --> 00:27:46.582
What exactly
are we talking about here?

499
00:27:46.623 --> 00:27:50.383
Look. I know you can’t just
take my word for it.

500
00:27:50.419 --> 00:27:52.799
I know you’re all asking.
where’s the proof?

501
00:27:52.838 --> 00:27:55.258
Where’s
the incontestable evidence?

502
00:27:55.299 --> 00:27:58.339
Well. I-I hear you.
I get it.

503
00:27:58.385 --> 00:28:02.755
Rest assured.
I’m still on that case.

504
00:28:02.806 --> 00:28:05.976
Right now I have a date with
the hottest guy in Hackensack.

505
00:28:06.018 --> 00:28:09.558
So. until next time. everyone
keep your eyes peeled.

506
00:28:09.605 --> 00:28:13.535
Our suspect is two feet tall.
has red hair. blue eyes.

507
00:28:13.567 --> 00:28:16.777
and should be considered
armed and extremely dangerous.

508
00:28:16.820 --> 00:28:20.780
[sirens wailing]

509
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:23.834
[indistinct chatter
over police radio]

510
00:28:23.869 --> 00:28:28.039
[dramatic music]

511
00:28:28.081 --> 00:28:29.291
- I’ll make a short statement

512
00:28:29.333 --> 00:28:31.463
before answering your questions.

513
00:28:31.501 --> 00:28:34.591
This afternoon at 4:12 p.m.
Eastern Standard Time

514
00:28:34.630 --> 00:28:36.840
in a bedroom
of the White House residence.

515
00:28:36.882 --> 00:28:40.262
a Secret Service agent
discharged his weapon.

516
00:28:40.302 --> 00:28:44.142
The agent in question was alone
at the time of the incident.

517
00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:46.351
and he fired a single shot.

518
00:28:46.391 --> 00:28:48.981
mortally wounding himself
in the process.

519
00:28:49.019 --> 00:28:51.309
The First Family was elsewhere
in the residence

520
00:28:51.355 --> 00:28:52.905
at the time of the shooting.

521
00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:56.480
They are all safe and request
that you respect their privacy

522
00:28:56.526 --> 00:28:59.356
in this time of grief.

523
00:28:59.404 --> 00:29:00.994
I’ll now take your questions.

524
00:29:01.031 --> 00:29:02.241
- Ms. Spiegel. Ms. Spiegel.

525
00:29:02.282 --> 00:29:03.992
- Uh. yes. gentleman
in the back.

526
00:29:04.034 --> 00:29:05.664
- This agent committed suicide?

527
00:29:05.702 --> 00:29:08.002
- Metropolitan Police
are investigating

528
00:29:08.038 --> 00:29:09.618
if it could be an accident.

529
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:12.675
But. yes. it appears this
tragedy was self-inflicted.

530
00:29:12.709 --> 00:29:15.169
- President Collins has
positioned this administration

531
00:29:15.212 --> 00:29:17.342
as one of utmost transparency.

532
00:29:17.381 --> 00:29:20.181
But given this scandal...

533
00:29:20.217 --> 00:29:23.047
Forgive me. this tragedy...

534
00:29:23.095 --> 00:29:26.065
Will the president honor
his promise to be completely

535
00:29:26.098 --> 00:29:29.228
and totally forthcoming?

536
00:29:29.268 --> 00:29:32.848
- The president feels that
difficult times such as these

537
00:29:32.896 --> 00:29:36.226
are exactly when openness
and honesty are needed most.

538
00:29:38.026 --> 00:29:41.026
Next question.
[reporters clamoring]

539
00:29:41.071 --> 00:29:45.371
♪ ♪

540
00:29:45.409 --> 00:29:48.329
[camera shutter clicking]

541
00:29:48.370 --> 00:29:54.040
♪ ♪

542
00:29:54.084 --> 00:29:56.884
[indistinct chatter]

543
00:29:56.920 --> 00:30:03.260
♪ ♪

544
00:30:03.302 --> 00:30:05.352
- Teddy left me.

545
00:30:05.387 --> 00:30:08.347
♪ ♪

546
00:30:08.390 --> 00:30:10.480
- Hey.

547
00:30:10.517 --> 00:30:13.387
Teddy would have done
anything for you.

548
00:30:13.437 --> 00:30:16.187
He just...

549
00:30:16.231 --> 00:30:18.231
he got sick.

550
00:30:18.275 --> 00:30:21.575
and we didn’t know about it.

551
00:30:21.611 --> 00:30:25.571
None of us knew.
Or we would have helped him.

552
00:30:25.615 --> 00:30:28.325
- Is Teddy going to come
back and haunt me. too?

553
00:30:28.368 --> 00:30:32.288
♪ ♪

554
00:30:32.331 --> 00:30:35.041
What about Joseph?
When can I have him back?

555
00:30:35.083 --> 00:30:36.253
- Oh. not yet. sweetheart.

556
00:30:36.293 --> 00:30:38.003
They need to do their job first.

557
00:30:38.045 --> 00:30:39.595
And we’ll get your doll.

558
00:30:39.629 --> 00:30:41.759
- Okay. listen to me.

559
00:30:41.798 --> 00:30:45.428
You’ve got to be brave.
all right. buddy?

560
00:30:45.469 --> 00:30:47.429
We’re going to get through this.

561
00:30:47.471 --> 00:30:49.061
All right?

562
00:30:51.308 --> 00:30:54.388
[indistinct chatter]

563
00:30:54.436 --> 00:31:00.186
♪ ♪

564
00:31:00.233 --> 00:31:01.943
- Joseph!

565
00:31:01.985 --> 00:31:05.605
♪ ♪

566
00:31:05.655 --> 00:31:08.825
Where am I going to sleep?

567
00:31:08.867 --> 00:31:11.617
- Your brother is going
to bunk with you tonight.

568
00:31:11.661 --> 00:31:14.621
- That’s okay.
I don’t mind.

569
00:31:14.664 --> 00:31:16.834
I think we both
could use the company.

570
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:23.629
- And what if I asked
how you were holding up?

571
00:31:23.673 --> 00:31:25.933
- Ah. come on. Hicks.

572
00:31:25.967 --> 00:31:28.427
Don’t start worrying
about me now.

573
00:31:28.470 --> 00:31:31.310
- Oh. believe me. I wouldn’t.
but it’s technically my job.

574
00:31:31.348 --> 00:31:33.138
and I have a condo to pay off.
- Right.

575
00:31:33.183 --> 00:31:34.733
Yeah. that condo.

576
00:31:34.768 --> 00:31:37.978
- Speaking of. were you...

577
00:31:38.021 --> 00:31:41.821
trying to get me fired
the other night?

578
00:31:41.858 --> 00:31:43.898
- Yeah. thanks
for not ratting me out.

579
00:31:43.944 --> 00:31:46.864
It’s very. like.
cool-substitute-teacher vibes...

580
00:31:46.905 --> 00:31:48.815
- This isn’t
a joking matter. Grant.

581
00:31:48.865 --> 00:31:49.985
I’m serious.

582
00:31:50.033 --> 00:31:52.123
You’re putting me
in a really tough spot.

583
00:31:56.540 --> 00:31:58.830
But I guess. uh...

584
00:31:58.875 --> 00:32:01.335
you’re in a tough spot.
too. right?

585
00:32:01.378 --> 00:32:05.668
♪ ♪

586
00:32:05.715 --> 00:32:08.885
- Can you imagine if my parents
knew I smoked weed

587
00:32:08.927 --> 00:32:13.637
here in these venerated halls
of American history?

588
00:32:13.682 --> 00:32:16.812
Heads up.
- I’d rather not.

589
00:32:16.852 --> 00:32:18.312
[chuckles]

590
00:32:18.353 --> 00:32:20.363
[water bubbling]

591
00:32:20.397 --> 00:32:26.897
♪ ♪

592
00:32:35.078 --> 00:32:38.538
- Maybe it’s
a little undignified.

593
00:32:38.582 --> 00:32:41.542
but at least
there’s still something secret.

594
00:32:41.585 --> 00:32:44.055
intimate between us.

595
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:46.667
even when nothing else
in our lives is private.

596
00:32:46.715 --> 00:32:48.635
not even our grief.

597
00:32:51.261 --> 00:32:52.391
- Teddy?

598
00:32:52.429 --> 00:32:54.139
- Yeah.
- [sighs]

599
00:32:54.181 --> 00:32:58.891
- I just keep thinking
about his wife. his kids.

600
00:32:58.935 --> 00:33:02.725
what they’re going through.

601
00:33:02.772 --> 00:33:06.482
James. I can’t imagine what
this is going to do to Henry.

602
00:33:09.446 --> 00:33:11.486
- We’re here for Henry.

603
00:33:12.866 --> 00:33:15.196
We’re here for each other.

604
00:33:16.786 --> 00:33:20.286
- What about that doll?
Both: Mm.

605
00:33:20.332 --> 00:33:21.712
- Are we doing the right thing

606
00:33:21.750 --> 00:33:25.500
letting him get
so attached to it?

607
00:33:25.545 --> 00:33:28.665
- Henry lost his brother.

608
00:33:28.715 --> 00:33:31.755
And he lost Teddy.

609
00:33:31.801 --> 00:33:34.511
Nothing we can do to fix that.

610
00:33:34.554 --> 00:33:37.564
I mean. it’s...
It’s never going to heal.

611
00:33:37.599 --> 00:33:40.139
So. if some doll

612
00:33:40.185 --> 00:33:44.615
gives him any sort
of comfort. then...

613
00:33:44.648 --> 00:33:47.278
who are we to take that
from him?

614
00:33:50.195 --> 00:33:52.245
- You’re stoned. aren’t you?

615
00:33:56.535 --> 00:33:59.505
[acoustic guitar music]

616
00:33:59.538 --> 00:34:06.668
♪ ♪

617
00:34:24.437 --> 00:34:27.437
- Elio. Elio. Elio.

618
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:31.492
♪ ♪

619
00:34:31.528 --> 00:34:34.568
- [smooches. chuckles]

620
00:34:34.614 --> 00:34:38.244
Oliver. Oliver. Oliver.

621
00:34:38.285 --> 00:34:42.505
♪ ♪

622
00:34:42.539 --> 00:34:44.499
- Are you nervous?

623
00:34:44.541 --> 00:34:48.671
- ♪ You don’t feel it now ♪

624
00:34:48.712 --> 00:34:52.052
- Oh. are we doing
"Titanic" now?

625
00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:55.640
Well. Jack. I’m a bit worried
about that iceberg up ahead.

626
00:34:57.387 --> 00:34:58.847
- Don’t worry.

627
00:34:58.888 --> 00:35:01.348
I made room for you
on my floating door.

628
00:35:01.391 --> 00:35:04.851
♪ ♪

629
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:07.064
[sighs] No. but. seriously.
are you nervous?

630
00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:09.515
- Terrified.
- [sighs] Me too.

631
00:35:09.566 --> 00:35:11.476
- [sighs] Thank God.

632
00:35:11.526 --> 00:35:14.316
- Do you want to stop?

633
00:35:14.362 --> 00:35:15.862
- Fuck it.
We’re ready.

634
00:35:15.905 --> 00:35:18.195
- Fuck. I love you.

635
00:35:18.241 --> 00:35:21.741
♪ ♪

636
00:35:21.786 --> 00:35:23.656
[cell phone chimes. vibrates]

637
00:35:23.705 --> 00:35:26.375
[both sigh heavily]
- Not now.

638
00:35:26.416 --> 00:35:30.876
- ♪ For a moment ♪

639
00:35:30.920 --> 00:35:34.840
- Devon. check your phone.

640
00:35:34.883 --> 00:35:37.553
- I think it’s Chucky.

641
00:35:37.594 --> 00:35:39.434
- "Still looking
for a Good Guy doll?

642
00:35:39.471 --> 00:35:41.601
"I know where you can find one.

643
00:35:41.640 --> 00:35:43.350
[sighs]
Amazingly lifelike."

644
00:35:43.391 --> 00:35:44.891
- "Looking for your sister?

645
00:35:44.934 --> 00:35:48.194
Maybe I can help.
I’m great with little kids."

646
00:35:50.106 --> 00:35:52.726
- Mine just says
"fuck you. Devon."

647
00:35:52.776 --> 00:35:55.606
[cell phone rings]

648
00:35:55.654 --> 00:35:58.664
- Hello?
- [chuckling evilly]

649
00:35:58.698 --> 00:36:00.578
You know. Jake...

650
00:36:00.617 --> 00:36:05.077
you have
a beautiful telephone voice.

651
00:36:05.121 --> 00:36:07.121
[chuckles]

652
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.415
♪ ♪

653
00:36:09.459 --> 00:36:10.999
- Chucky.

654
00:36:11.044 --> 00:36:13.464
- You bitches miss me?

655
00:36:13.505 --> 00:36:15.595
- Yeah. we missed you.

656
00:36:15.632 --> 00:36:18.432
Tell us where you are.
and we’ll come visit right now.

657
00:36:18.468 --> 00:36:19.928
- Nah. you know me.

658
00:36:19.969 --> 00:36:22.929
I’m more of a hide-and-seek
kind of a guy.

659
00:36:22.972 --> 00:36:27.232
[chuckles]
Besides. my new place

660
00:36:27.268 --> 00:36:30.808
is pretty strict about visitors.

661
00:36:32.065 --> 00:36:34.945
- Okay. Chucky.
you want to play?

662
00:36:34.984 --> 00:36:38.204
Let’s play. but give us a clue.

663
00:36:38.238 --> 00:36:39.778
- I just did.

664
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:42.873
[suspenseful music]

665
00:36:42.909 --> 00:36:50.039
♪ ♪

666
00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:58.041
- Okay. I wrote
this test last night.

667
00:37:00.677 --> 00:37:05.387
Covers English. history.
geometry. biology.

668
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:08.142
I-I even threw in a little bit
of driver’s ed.

669
00:37:08.184 --> 00:37:10.234
- You’re saying this
like it’s a good thing.

670
00:37:10.270 --> 00:37:13.400
- Come on. guys. we are two
months into the school year.

671
00:37:13.440 --> 00:37:15.020
We’ve barely cracked a book.

672
00:37:15.066 --> 00:37:18.646
I need to know where you’re at.
educationally speaking.

673
00:37:18.695 --> 00:37:20.455
[sighs]
With everything that happened.

674
00:37:20.488 --> 00:37:22.818
all of the classes
you’ve missed. I just...

675
00:37:22.866 --> 00:37:25.656
I don’t want you to end up...
[sighs]

676
00:37:25.702 --> 00:37:28.002
- Falling behind?

677
00:37:28.037 --> 00:37:29.407
- Stupid.

678
00:37:31.416 --> 00:37:34.586
Now. eyes on your own papers.
Call me when you’re done.

679
00:37:34.627 --> 00:37:37.587
[dramatic music]

680
00:37:37.630 --> 00:37:39.170
♪ ♪

681
00:37:39.215 --> 00:37:41.585
- You think we should tell her
Chucky’s back?

682
00:37:41.634 --> 00:37:43.264
- So she can add it to the test?

683
00:37:43.303 --> 00:37:44.603
- We can’t.

684
00:37:44.637 --> 00:37:46.467
It’s too dangerous.

685
00:37:46.514 --> 00:37:48.434
I mean. she’s done everything
she can to help us.

686
00:37:48.475 --> 00:37:50.435
The least we can do
is try to protect her.

687
00:37:50.477 --> 00:37:52.647
- Hey. I can hear you
whispering in there.

688
00:37:52.687 --> 00:37:56.477
Less chatty. more testy.

689
00:37:56.524 --> 00:37:58.694
[thunder rumbles. rain falling]

690
00:37:58.735 --> 00:38:02.495
- None of us face
the pain of loss alone.

691
00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.910
We are lifted up by community.

692
00:38:04.949 --> 00:38:07.029
We lean on our loved ones.

693
00:38:07.076 --> 00:38:11.706
And we let Him carry us
during times of unease.

694
00:38:11.748 --> 00:38:14.828
As we celebrate the life
of Theodore Brooks.

695
00:38:14.876 --> 00:38:17.706
we can take comfort in Psalm 23.

696
00:38:17.754 --> 00:38:19.134
[camera shutters clicking]

697
00:38:19.172 --> 00:38:21.722
Yea. though I walk
through the valley

698
00:38:21.758 --> 00:38:24.298
of the shadow of death.

699
00:38:24.344 --> 00:38:27.474
I will fear no evil.

700
00:38:27.514 --> 00:38:29.724
Good men.

701
00:38:29.766 --> 00:38:32.596
men of honor like Teddy.

702
00:38:32.644 --> 00:38:36.404
need never fear evil.

703
00:38:36.439 --> 00:38:41.239
For he shall dwell in
the House of the Lord forever.

704
00:38:41.277 --> 00:38:42.737
Amen.

705
00:38:42.779 --> 00:38:49.659
♪ ♪

706
00:38:49.702 --> 00:38:51.752
- Ready...

707
00:38:51.788 --> 00:38:53.958
aim. fire.

708
00:38:53.998 --> 00:38:55.328
[gunshots]
- [gasps]

709
00:38:55.375 --> 00:38:57.465
Ready...

710
00:38:57.502 --> 00:38:59.342
aim. fire.

711
00:38:59.379 --> 00:39:00.759
[gunshots]

712
00:39:00.797 --> 00:39:03.417
Ready. aim. fire.

713
00:39:03.466 --> 00:39:05.376
[gunshots]

714
00:39:05.426 --> 00:39:12.306
♪ ♪

715
00:39:14.811 --> 00:39:18.271
[indistinct chatter]

716
00:39:23.236 --> 00:39:26.316
- Pulled those bank statements
you asked for.

717
00:39:26.364 --> 00:39:30.494
♪ ♪

718
00:39:30.535 --> 00:39:34.585
- Just wondering if you wanted
to broadcast that any louder?

719
00:39:34.622 --> 00:39:36.792
♪ ♪

720
00:39:36.833 --> 00:39:39.173
- Your Secret Service friend
up there...

721
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:43.630
Totally clean. no red flags.

722
00:39:43.673 --> 00:39:46.223
- How about large
cash withdrawals?

723
00:39:46.259 --> 00:39:48.679
Maybe he had a habit.
- Ah. he’s a Boy Scout.

724
00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:51.180
He was always a Boy Scout.
What... what do you expect?

725
00:39:51.222 --> 00:39:52.812
- Any big purchases at all?

726
00:39:52.849 --> 00:39:55.519
Something besides milk
and preschool?

727
00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:57.650
- Yeah. kind of.

728
00:39:57.687 --> 00:39:59.357
A couple of days before he died.

729
00:39:59.397 --> 00:40:02.727
he put a down payment
on a cruise line...

730
00:40:02.775 --> 00:40:05.355
Trip to Alaska with his wife.

731
00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:08.413
- You’re on a government
salary. two young kids.

732
00:40:08.448 --> 00:40:11.528
would you put money down
on an expensive trip

733
00:40:11.576 --> 00:40:15.996
if you already had your bags
packed for the great beyond?

734
00:40:16.039 --> 00:40:18.999
- You know what?
The less I know. the better.

735
00:40:19.042 --> 00:40:25.882
♪ ♪

736
00:40:38.186 --> 00:40:40.646
- [sighs]

737
00:40:40.688 --> 00:40:44.358
♪ ♪

738
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:46.530
- Okay. so what do
we have on Chucky?

739
00:40:46.569 --> 00:40:48.699
- Honestly. nothing.

740
00:40:48.738 --> 00:40:51.368
We’ve scoured the Internet
and all of Hackensack

741
00:40:51.407 --> 00:40:55.077
for almost a year and found
literally no sign of him.

742
00:40:55.119 --> 00:40:57.869
If Chucky hadn’t called us.
we’d have nothing at all.

743
00:40:57.914 --> 00:40:59.874
- The phone call
is the one clue we do have.

744
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:02.126
You saw the number right?
It was all zeros.

745
00:41:02.168 --> 00:41:04.168
- Yeah.
- I did some digging.

746
00:41:04.212 --> 00:41:06.342
Let’s say you want to block
your number. easy.

747
00:41:06.381 --> 00:41:09.631
But what if you’re so private.
so important...

748
00:41:09.676 --> 00:41:11.756
- Wait. How important?

749
00:41:11.803 --> 00:41:14.353
Like Zendaya?

750
00:41:14.389 --> 00:41:16.059
- So important
that you can make it

751
00:41:16.099 --> 00:41:18.099
like your number
doesn’t even exist at all?

752
00:41:18.142 --> 00:41:20.562
- So who are we talking about...
Like. the government?

753
00:41:20.603 --> 00:41:22.103
- Exactly.

754
00:41:22.146 --> 00:41:24.208
I looked it up. And the only
people with that kind of power

755
00:41:24.232 --> 00:41:26.232
are. like. the Pentagon
and the CIA.

756
00:41:26.275 --> 00:41:29.395
- So. um. would you say
we did pretty good?

757
00:41:29.445 --> 00:41:32.235
- Pretty well.

758
00:41:32.281 --> 00:41:34.331
- We did?

759
00:41:34.367 --> 00:41:36.387
- [sighs] God. no. I was just
correcting your grammar.

760
00:41:36.411 --> 00:41:40.541
Unfortunately. you guys
are way behind your peers.

761
00:41:40.581 --> 00:41:43.541
We have a lot
of catching up to do.

762
00:41:43.584 --> 00:41:45.134
But fret not.

763
00:41:45.169 --> 00:41:49.549
I am going to mold
those squishy little minds

764
00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:51.930
into founts of knowledge.

765
00:41:51.968 --> 00:41:53.758
- Sounds a little painful.

766
00:41:53.803 --> 00:41:56.433
- I’m going to go start
on a lesson plan...

767
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:58.102
and a glass of wine.

768
00:41:58.141 --> 00:42:02.941
♪ ♪

769
00:42:02.979 --> 00:42:05.189
- Holy shit.

770
00:42:06.941 --> 00:42:09.531
- since Joseph Collins’
tragic death last winter

771
00:42:09.569 --> 00:42:12.489
and the first-ever
apparent suicide.

772
00:42:12.530 --> 00:42:15.490
A sadly historic situation.
indeed.

773
00:42:15.533 --> 00:42:17.873
The First Family now returning
to the White House

774
00:42:17.910 --> 00:42:20.120
from the departed agent’s
memorial service.

775
00:42:20.163 --> 00:42:21.963
- White House.

776
00:42:21.998 --> 00:42:26.958
Chucky in the White House?

